weather_srv
DLR 2009 Jul 8

souce scripts and code for the weather server, running on quest16. All
code must reside in /home/observer/palomar/weather_srv


weather_srv.pl : perl script to take socket commands (mostly just the "s" command") and return dome status at La Silla through the socket. It uses wget to read a file called "dome.last" from another machine at La Silla. The script must run on quest16 since that is the only machine on the La Silla network. It reads
the dome.last file and checks to see if the log time is current, and if the
dome states for both the NTT and the 2.2-m are open. If so, it returns the
date and the word "OPEN". If the log time is current, and both domes are
closed, it returns "CLOSED". If one dome is closed and the other is open, it
returns "UNCERTAIN". If it can not determine either dome's state, or the
log time is not current, it returns ERROR.

weather_client.pl : the client perl script that takes a command as standard input (typically "s"), sends it over a socket to the weather_srv.pl server, reads the result back over the socket, and writes it to standard output

weather_srv.cfg :  configuration file for the server or client. It gives  the 
IP number of the machine running the server, and the socket port number to use
for communication.

ntt_dome_status: this is a csh script called by weather_srv.pl to run wget
and interpret the dome.last file

date_to_time.c : a C progam to convert yyyy mm dd hh mm ss to times since
Jan 1, 1970 00:00:00.  To compile, type "make date_to_time".


